	('B010FAU07W', 'Healthy, strong bones have one thing in common: calcium and vitamin D. When you dont get enough calcium from your diet, calcium supplements can help fill the gaps. Vitamin D is needed by the body for calcium absorption, so your supplement should include vitamin D as well. Caltrate calcium supplements, including Soft Chews and Gummy Bites, have the most vitamin D3 to help maximize calcium absorption and nourish strong, healthy bones*.'),
	('B010FAU07W', 'Calcium supports more than just bone health. When you bend your leg, arm or move almost any bone, your muscles and joints are working with your bones to help you keep going. So it only makes sense that you want to keep muscles flexible and healthy, too. Caltrate 600 plus D3 supplements provide the calcium and vitamin D to support healthy bones and muscles to keep you moving throughout life.*'),
	('B010FAU07W', 'Among the important things vitamin D does is to help maximize your body&#039;s ability to absorb calcium. A deficiency in vitamin D means your bones cant absorb the calcium needed to maintain bone mass. Since sources of vitamin D are limited, Caltrate 600 plus D3 calcium and vitamin D3 supplements are a great way to ensure youre getting the recommended daily amount for bone health.*'),
	('B010FAU07W', 'Osteoporosis can occur due to low bone mass and bone tissue deterioration, leading to brittle, fragile bones that are susceptible to breaking. Maintaining adequate calcium and vitamin D throughout life, as part of a well balanced and healthy diet, may reduce the risk of osteoporosis and related fractures. Adding Caltrate to your healthy routine, at any age, is an easy way to get the calcium and vitamin D you need to maintain strong bones.*'),
	('B010FAU07W', 'You know you need calcium to help keep bones strong, but did you know that not all calcium is the same? The calcium supplements that you turn to fill your nutritional needs are often made of one of two forms: calcium carbonate or calcium citrate. Calcium carbonate, the form found in most of our Caltrate products, is more concentrated and provides the same amount of calcium in a smaller-sized tablet than products using calcium citrate.'),
	('B010FAU8MO', 'The active ingredient in Advil Liqui-Gels, Ibuprofen, is already dissolved in a soft gelatin capsule.'),
