	('0786635290', 'Richard Kriehn was born in Houston, Texas. He started playing mandolin at the age of ten. That same year, he was introduced to the violin through the public school string program. After high school. He attended Sam Houston State University in Huntsville, Texas, to study classical violin. During his sophomore year, he entered and won first place in the Buck White International Mandolin Contest (1985).'),
	('0801098939', '<b>Kenneth J. Collins</b> (PhD, Drew University) is professor of historical theology and Wesley studies at Asbury Theological Seminary in Wilmore, Kentucky.<br /><br /><b>Jerry L. Walls</b> (PhD, University of Notre Dame) is professor of philosophy and scholar in residence at Houston Baptist University in Houston, Texas.'),
